So far at the UW I haven't really accomplished anything that I wanted to accomplish when I first started going there.  My GPA is way low I've failed a class and been forced to drop another and I don't have the clear goals I thought I did involving what I wanted to do.  So today I took the initiative and enrolled at Cascadia Community College.  I've done this so I can get my associates degree in computer science and hopefully transfer back to the UW after I receive it.  I will only need to take about 3 quarters at CCC so I should be back at the UW in spring of next year working on my bachelors degree.  With any luck this new strategy will work out since I will have small class sizes and will have more access to my teachers.  All that is left to do is take a leave of absence from the UW and I will be on my way to what I hope will be a better college experience than what I have experienced so far.

You know what i hate?  how people say Lord of the RIngs is the greatest fantasy series ever and talk about how great of writer Tolkien was.  I will admit the fact that Lord of the Rings was a good series, but it definatly wasnt great.  It was slow paced and boring throughout the majority of the books.  Also people talk about how Tolkien described things with minimal detail.  To those people i say go back and READ Lord of the Rings because Tolkien definatly wastes pages on description.  Also if your going to write a review of the book DONT REFERENCE THE MOVIES!  good god people the movies were mostly terrible and dont even come close to the actual books.  In my opinion there are much better fantasy novels and series out there.  I wont flat out say skip Lord of the Rings but there are plenty of other, better, books to read out there.

Also i hate how people say Nirvana is the best grunge band ever, because there were quite a few better grunge bands than Nirvana, Alice In Chains and Soundgarden to name a few.  As Grant Kimura once said, "Theres more to grunge than Kurt Cobain."

In conclusion, although Lord of the Rings was the first popular fantasy series its definatly not the best.  And although Nirvana was the first mainstream grunge band it also is not the best.

so yeah... school... im pretty sure ive taken school for granted pretty much my entire life... all through elementry school, junior high and highschool i havent had to put forth much effort at all... i mean i litteraly coasted through highschool with my 3.6 and didnt even really try... i suppose i have gotten so used to the fact that i didnt have to study that i cant even bring myself to study for classes i know i should study for in college...  every time i sit down to study i think to myself, "why should you study, you didnt have to study in highschool" and of course i answer myself with the typical moral boosting responce of, "maybe you arnt as smart as you thought you were." the thing here is i am so used to things being easy that the thought of having to put forth effort scares me... not just in school but in life too... if something prooves difficult i dont do it, or i just ignore it.  because lets face it, i am smart, its not like ive gotten less smart since highschool... the only thing thats changed is that classes have gotten harder and im still putting forth my minimal effort... if i dont understand something i bitch and complain about not understanding it but i really cant be bothered to look it up in a book... and im to arrogant to ask for help from friends or a TA because i feel that if i ask for help that somehow makes me less intelligent than the person im asking for help from and i cant stand that feeling... so here i am in college to stuck up to ask for help and to lazy to study... and barley passing my classes... i suppose i could blame this on my highschool or something for "not preparing me for college" but really the only person i can blame here is myself because i am to lazy to try... maybe after im done with physics i wont have to worry about this anymore and ill be able to just coast through classes like i used to be able to... but then again... maybe i wont... and you know whats sad... i bought a $150 physics text book at the beginning of the quarter and i havent even opened it... ITS STILL IN ITS FREEKING PLASTIC WRAP!!! god i piss myself off... oh well

ASo about an hour ago to two hours ago i had at least 8 loaded guns pointed at me, and at least 2 of which were M16s and 1 was some kinds shotgun.  I was aslo forced to the ground, handcuffed and put into the back of a police SUV.  Here is that story.

So Bryan, Dustin and I, after watching "You Only Live Twice" desided we should leave my house so Sam could get some sleep since he has to work early.  After leaving my house we desided we should make a movie with the fake guns they brought over.  First we went to the gas station though so Dustin could get gas.  After that we drove down to the buisness park near Canyon Park to use the streat lamps for light in our movie, because lets face it, its dark outside at 11pm. APPARENTLY someone saw us with the guns though and called the police.  So at 11:30pm 4 cop cars pull in with lights flashing and a cop SUV comes in as well.  All the doors fly open and cops jump out with guns and start yelling at us to put our hands on our heads.  They told us to keep our hands out of out pockets and to put them on our heads, but Bryan being the genious he is, thought they told us to empty our pockets so he put his hands back in.  At which point they started yelling and every single one of them drew a gun and pointed it at us.  Well at that point they had us come forward one a time and handcuffed us, and put us into seperate cars.  They then started asking me about the guns so i told them they were fake and that we were filming a moive.  They then searched our cars and found the guns, which were 2 fake 6 shooters, an airsoft handgun that looks almost real, and a paintball gun. Once they determined it was all a misunderstanding they sat us down on the curb took off our handcuffs and talked to us about being stupid.  And then they let us go.  All in all it was pretty enertaining since the only one of us who was really that scared was Bryan.  He was FREAKING out.  While Dustin and I for the most part just realised it was a misunderstanding and managed to remain mostly calm.

Interesting start to the day if i do say so myself.

Thursday So REALLY early thursday morning(like 12:30am) grant imed me telling me about a beach party at golden gardens the next day at 3... and then he told me i should come... so i decided i would go... so at like 2:30 the next day i picked ashlyn up and we headed to golden gardens... when we got there only 3 of the people had shown up and grant wasnt among them so we just chilled with igor and joe and some other dude i didnt know for a while... then we made hamburgers... right as we were finishing eating grant and melissa(i think thats her name... either that or marissa) and some other dude showed up... so they made burgers... and yeah... it was cool... after a while breanna showed up so we were all just chillin... we also put up some weird tent thing because it had started to rain but it stoped so we took it down after a while... then we went and had a fire in one of the fire pits... i think Igor had way to much fun with the lighter fluid at this point because he used like the rest of the can... then we just chilled around the fire till it was almost out... and then we all parted ways... there are lots of pictures on Igors facebook for those of you who have facebook... after that ashlyn and i went back to her dorm where i ended up crashing for the night.. Friday I woke up at like 10:30 or w/e smelling like a campfire and decided i should prolly head home so i said goodbye to ashlyn and left... upon arriving home i took a shower and started reading... after reading for like 2 hours i got up and took ANOTHER shower because i still smelled like a campfire... at about 6 i picked ashlyn up at the YMCA and drove to jordans for his party... we ended up chilling there till like 12 playing kickball and watching movies... while we were playing kickball sam was foolishly tossed over a barbed wire fence into a mass of blackberry bushes in order to retreave the ball, which he did... and ended up not being hurt at all... which was pretty amazing... Sunday Well today i woke up early and took my car to the shop to get an oilchange and to get the radiator looked at cuz something is up with it... and after that i just chilled at my house talking with my grandma and reading untill like 5:30 or 6 or so when ashlyn called me... at that point i went and picked her up... then we went back to my house for my cousin andrea's college graduation party... which was fun, cuz i found out two of my moms cousins had been arrested for robbing banks... i have an awesome family... then we just talked to my uncle matt for a while about engineering and such untill 9 when i took ashlyn to the airport =(... shes gone for like 10 days or so visiting her family... after that i came back home and chilled and talked to my cousin and aunt and dad for a while till my uncle matt, aunt judy, and andrea left... so now here i am updating this for the last few days of my life... so yeah, peace kids

seriously though ashlyn is an awesome g/f... ive never actually met someone who decided that they would kill me without a second thought given the chance... its pretty sweet... taking over the world just got a ton more interesting =)

Friday:
So i woke up and went to school... same as everyother day lol... but i decided to see if ashlyn wanted to come over and chill after school so i called her and she was like sure ill come over after i turn in some job applications...  then i went home... at home i promptly realised bryan was at my house... so i went inside and demanded that we go see X3 that night... and bryan being the smart man that he is, readily agreed... we decided to go see the 9:40 showing so since it was like 4 we had some time to kill... i started working on my programming homework and finished my HuffmanTree class which means i have like 85% of the assignment left to do lol... then ashlyn called me to tell me she was at cascadia so i went and picked her up... after arriving back at mu house we all just chillaxed and messed around with my dads digital camera.  then my dad decided we all needed to go to this pizza restraunt in Clearview so we packed into 2 cars and drove down there... on the way i took mass cool pictures of us while we were inside the car... plus a buch of really cool AirGuitar pictures lol... once we arrived there the guy was like SORRY GUYS but we close in like 20min... but since your cool ill make you pizza and you can take them home... so me, ashlyn, sam and bryan piled back into the car we took and drove back home where we just chillaxed till the food arived... after that we ate the pizza and left to go see X3... at this point is when i grabbed my awesome blue hat that i used to wear all the time (I FOUND IT!!!! <3 <3 <3) and ashlyn grabbed the purple imitation blue hat... once arriving in woodinville we proceeded to try and protect our hats from sam and bryan who wanted to destroy them... X3 was a very good movie so you should all go see it... watch all the credits too cuz theres a cool little extra sceen after them... after the movie we just went back to my house and chilled till like 3 when we all just crashed...

tuesday and wednesday nothing terribly exciting happened except that on tuesday i failed a math midterm and on wednesday i failed a chem mid term... so yeah...

thursday i skiped math cuz i didnt feel like going and then should have skiped chemistry cuz it was a lab lecture but i didnt cuz i had to wait for steven and ashlyn to get out of class anyways... then after school we went and picked up alex and went out in stevens boat... first off launching the boat proved difficult cuz there was this werid yellow floaty thing on the water that was in our way... but we managed to avoid that... then stevens boat wouldnt start... so he spent like 20 min trying to fix it untill it started... then we went and chilled in his boat by juanita beach for like an hour... then alex decided he wanted to go intertubing... but the boat wouldnt start... so steven spent like an hour trying to get it to work untill it eventually did... after that steven and i decided to teach me to learn to pull skiers and wakeboarders so we spent the next 30 or so min teaching me to pull people... after that steven decided to start trying to throw people off the boat... i didnt help alex when steven decided to throw him over so he decided that i had to be taught a lesson... so he shot me with steven water gun thing... after we got back we chilled in the hot tub untill steven kicked us out of his house cuz he had to leave...

friday i went to school and chilled till i had to go home... then at like 6 i left to go pick up ashlyn for the concert but it took me like an hour to get there since i misjudged trafic... and then it took us forever to find the club it was at cuz it was hidden away in a back corner thats about impossible to find... but the concert was amazing... of the two opening bands The Divorce were freaking amazing and The Feaver were ok... and then The (International) Noice Conspiracy were just awesome... it was pretty freaking awesome... after that we went back to my house and chillaxed with sam and watched better off dead... which is a great movie btw... and then we just chrashed here...

yesterday we just hung out around my house till about 1 or so when we went and rented 3 movies... Bill and Teds Excellent Adventure, Kung-Pow, and Spiders 2... we tryed to watch Kung-Pow but it didnt work so we watched Bill and Teds Excellent Adventure... which is ANOTHER great movie... bryan showed up about halfway threw that movie and afterwords we went out for lunch at qdoba... then we came back to my house and watched Spiders 2... which is an AMAZINGLY horrible horror film about spiders that was HILARIOUS cuz of how retarted everyone was... so yeah... go rent that movie cuz its awesome... then we just sat around my house chilling and trying to figure out what to do... we ate dinner with my family and then decided to go see Mission Impossible 3 at 10:20... and i must say... that movie was pretty good... then we just chillaxed here till about 2 when bryan left and i took ashlyn home...

today ive just been chilling doing nothing and reading and its been fun... so yeah... peace

when you examine my life you will find many interesting ideas that if properly put into action could probably save the world tons of money, keep little kids occupied and make the world a more peaceful place.  It really is to bad no one takes the time to properly think about my ideas and put them in the right contex.  Oh well, thats why one day i will rule the world and you will all be my slaves.

anyways i havent REALLY talked about anything in here for a long time and i figure now is a good of time as any for a halfway decent post about my life, expecially since i cant sleep cuz im thinking way to much.  I always find it facinating when for the first half of the day i struggle to stay awake and after 7 i would do anything to go to sleep. Oh well, sucks to be me i guess.

So first things first im gonna talk about my day.  Today was a pretty good day.  I got enough sleep last night so i wasnt AS tired as i normally am.  I managed to stay awake threw all of my classes.  I ACTUALLY sat outside today at school and enjoyed it, which doesnt happen very much.  Of course that only lasted till steven saw me and came over and started talking to me.  I mean i like steven but DAMN sometimes he has the worst timing.  Well after he got there it wasnt peaceful and quiet anymore so it kinda defeated the purpose of being outside but i dealt with it.  Then he called ashlyn and so we just chilled outside till we had to go to class.  After that i went home and tried to chill with sam but he was snappy so i gave up on that and just went upstairs and talked to my dad about all the things i should have done in highschool.  Then at like 7 i went over and chilled with steven and ashlyn at stevens house.  Then sara came over and they started making out on the couch i was sitting on so i was like screw that and went to get wheatthins.  To bad they were weird tomato ones so i about died when i ate them.  After a while my neck started to hurt so i took some ibuprofin(sp?) and then managed to secure the couch when steven and sara got up to get something to eat.  So we watched tv mostly and talked and steven and i got in a sandle fight with ashlyns sandles which was pretty fun. And then i went home at like 1 or so, so here i am.  And on reflection of my day i think overall it was a good day.

I am also pretty happy with the way my life is going right now, I have a bunch of good friends and people i can trust without worring about things.  School is great for the most part, although chemistry can be a bitch.  I feel good for the most part none of that emotional crap i was going threw last year and so everything seems pretty damn good to me.  Although it would be more fun if like neal and andrew came home more often, and if they called me when they did. Plus i picked out new glasses yesterday so i should be getting those soon, which means first off that i will have sunglasses since this pare comes with sunglass attachments, and second off means taht i wont have to wear contacts all the time anymore which i might actually miss since ive started getting used to them.
